Beginning Monday June 7th motorists traveling over US 2 Stevens Pass should expect up to 20 minute delays as they encounter lane shifts and occasional flagger or pilot car controlled traffic due to a paving project. The hours for this project are Mon-Thur 6 a.m. to 6 p.m. The work zone for this project extends from milepost 62 two and a half miles west of the summit to milepost 71 on the east side of Stevens Pass. US 2 Paving (Stevens Pass)County: Chelan Highway: US 2 Region: North CentralLocation: MP 62-70Description: A crew is paving nine miles of deteriorated road over the summit of Steven Pass. This work is weather dependent.Work schedule: Monday through Thursday from 6 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. traffic in each direction will be reduced to 1 lane. Expect slow downs and longer than normal travel times during working hours. The crew may require intermittent traffic control with flaggers when staging equipment and setting up lane closures.Contact: NCR Communications 509-860-0000
